goals.question: What is the correlation between year and net generation?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of year and net generation
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a relationship between year and net generation.

goals.question: What is the distribution of net generation?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of net generation values and identify any outliers.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.title('What is the trend of net generation over the years?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sources = data['source'].unique()
    colors = ['blue', 'green', 'red']
    for i, source in enumerate(sources):
        source_data = data[data['source'] == source]
        ax.bar(source_data['year'], source_data['net_generation'], color=colors[i], label=source)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].mean().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values('net_generation', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.barh(data['source'], data['net_generation'], color='green')
    ax.set_xlabel('Average Net Generation')
    ax.set_ylabel('Source')
    ax.set_title('What is the average net generation by source?')
    for i, v in enumerate(data['net_generation']):
        ax.text(v + 500, i - 0.1, str(round(v, 2)), color='black', fontweight='bold')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['year'], data['net_generation'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between year and net generation?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['net_generation'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['net_generation'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['net_generation'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Net Generation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
